I'm positive that doing that was responsible for a large number of supports.\r\n\r\n\"If you do everything right your project should sell itself by people spreading the word for you.\" - Boom. see it as a set.  \nSo nice pictures (for digital, rendered) of your project are very important, this is whats going get people to click on your project to see more. It is apparent that the topic of minifigures vs minidolls is ongoing and could easily become a passionate debate. I personally love them both. I have a little girl and two boys. When the Friends sets came out, my daughter was at just about the right age to start playing with small toys and she had grown into seeing her older brothers play with Lego. Me and my wife were so excited to see a different take on minifigures geared towards girls and my daughter was immediately interested whereas with the minifigures of old, she was just like your daughter in the sense that she felt they could be \"ugly\" at times. Again, this is just one's opinion. It was a big decision for me to decide to go with minidolls on this but in the end I had to go with what I felt was the most viable for the demographic of the Frozen brand and the likelihood of what I felt Lego would choose had they designed this set themselves (WWLD-what would Lego do?). I really wish Lego released sets with the option of either minidoll or minifigures, unfortunately they don't. So given my time constraints and the pattern with which Lego has set in the past I made my decision to give Lego the best ready-to-go or as close to a finalized product as I could come should they choose to commercialize my design idea. If they crunch the numbers and see that somehow minifigures will be better and/or most profitable, then I'll be one of the first to be excited at what they do with them. This whole topic is indicative of one major thing...Frozen is popular with everyone of all genders and ages and there isn't one all-satisfying minifigure just yet."}, "subject": {"type": "user", "uuid": "ccbffbc0-5e88-47e4-901d-c8aac63aa42c", "display": "Fohzen"}}, {"timestamp": 1399337161000, "verb": "comment:reply", "id": 5118992, "object": {"owner": {"type": "user", "uuid": "ccbffbc0-5e88-47e4-901d-c8aac63aa42c", "display": "Fohzen"}, "object": {"owner": {"type": "user", "uuid": "8f4c97cc-52d0-4f74-bf51-7cda56fd1109", "display": "7-ate-9"}, "object": "2ce2f3f5-7b82-4909-9bf2-5635c9908450", "type": "comment", "uuid": "6a9f4c32-1e33-4b16-afce-cb4a53cb4bd1", "display": null}, "type": "comment", "uuid": "eb929da5-4627-4ac4-b26b-f5b006de3350", "display": "Thank you for seeing my logic!
